The paper deals with the problem of range capture of 3D objects using multiple projectors and cameras, which is a common topic in computer vision and graphics. The use of structured light and projector-camera triangulation suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also deals with the problem of disambiguating multiple projectors, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a novel method for multi-projector color structured-light vision, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
